From abbe7f7598f2600d0262ef8fad85995491f2c9a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 22:35:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] selinux_adapter: skip selabel_open when no file_contexts
 files found

When running in a container with SELinux disabled (build_selinux=false),
the file_contexts paths may not exist. If no options are assembled, calling
selabel_open() crashes with a NULL-dereference. Guard against this by
returning early when index==0.

Part of Phase 1 (infrastructure & target setup) for hybris_generic:
SELinux is fully disabled for container operation; the Ubuntu Touch host
manages the SELinux policy.

Change-Id: I091fc1833af2b6fb653eecb076b7c69ea61b8197
---
 framework/policycoreutils/src/selinux_restorecon.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/framework/policycoreutils/src/selinux_restorecon.c b/framework/policycoreutils/src/selinux_restorecon.c
index 5e00d1895..3b1dada1b 100644
--- a/framework/policycoreutils/src/selinux_restorecon.c
+++ b/framework/policycoreutils/src/selinux_restorecon.c
@@ -51,6 +51,12 @@ static void SetFileContextsHandle(void)
         options[index++] = vendorOption;
     }
 
+    if (index == 0) {
+        // No file_contexts files found - skip selabel_open to avoid crash in container/SELinux-disabled environments
+        selinux_log(SELINUX_WARNING, "No file_contexts files found, skipping restorecon handle init\n");
+        return;
+    }
+
     // default option of selabel_open
     SelinuxOptions digestOption = {SELABEL_OPT_DIGEST, (char *)1};
     options[index++] = digestOption;
-- 
2.50.1

